<!-- Sonority Sound — Support & FAQ -->
<div class="sp-wrap">

  <div class="sp-glow"></div>

  <!-- ── Hero ── -->
  <div class="sp-hero">
    <p class="sp-eyebrow">Sonority Sound</p>
    <h1 class="sp-hero__title">Support & FAQ</h1>
    <p class="sp-hero__sub">Answers to the most common questions — before you need to send an email.</p>
    <div class="sp-hero__search-hint">
      <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#c9a84c" stroke-width="1.8"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><path d="m21 21-4.35-4.35"/></svg>
      10 questions covered below
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── FAQ Grid ── -->
  <div class="sp-faq">
  <div class="sp-faq__inner">

    <!-- Q1 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">01</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">Can I use these sounds commercially as an individual creator?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>Yes — absolutely. Every purchase automatically comes with a full Individual License that covers commercial use. This includes monetised YouTube, Instagram, TikTok, and other social channels, paid client video projects, advertising campaigns, broadcast content, and any other project where you earn revenue. You pay once, and you're covered for life across every platform. No royalties, no attribution required, no strings attached. The only thing you cannot do is resell or redistribute the raw audio files themselves.</p>
        <a href="/pages/licensing" class="sp-item__link">Read the full licensing terms →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q2 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">02</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">I work in a studio or agency with multiple editors — what license do I need?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>If multiple people within your team, agency, or production house will be accessing and using the sounds — you'll need a Teams & Studio License rather than an Individual License. We don't use fixed pricing for studios; instead, we work out a fair agreement based on your team size, how you use the sounds, and the scale of your projects. To get started, simply email us with a brief description of your team and how you work — we'll come back to you within 24 hours with a quote.</p>
        <a href="mailto:benntkmanagement@gmail.com?subject=Teams%20%26%20Studio%20License%20Enquiry" class="sp-item__link">Email us for a studio quote →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q3 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">03</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">Do I own the sounds forever after purchasing?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>Yes. Your license is perpetual — it never expires. Once you purchase a pack, it's yours to use forever across any project you create, now or in the future. There are no subscription fees, no renewal costs, and no annual charges. You pay once and you're done. Your purchased files will always be available to re-download from your account at any time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q4 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">04</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">If a pack gets updated in the future, do I get the updated version?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>Yes — if we release an update to a pack you've already purchased, you'll receive access to the updated version at no additional cost. We believe in rewarding our existing customers. If a significant update is released to a pack you own, we'll make the updated files available to you. If you're unsure whether you're on the latest version of a pack you've purchased, email us with your order number and we'll sort it out for you.</p>
        <a href="mailto:benntkmanagement@gmail.com?subject=Pack%20Update%20Enquiry" class="sp-item__link">Contact us about a pack update →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q5 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">05</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">What if I purchased the wrong product by mistake?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>If you purchased the wrong pack, get in touch with us as soon as possible — ideally before downloading the files. Email us your order number and let us know which pack you intended to buy. We'll do our best to swap it over for the correct one. We can't guarantee this in every case (especially if files have already been accessed), but we'll always try to find a fair solution. Acting quickly gives us the best chance to help.</p>
        <a href="mailto:benntkmanagement@gmail.com?subject=Wrong%20Product%20Purchased" class="sp-item__link">Contact us about your order →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q6 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">06</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">What if I'm unsatisfied with my purchase?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>We're proud of the quality and authenticity of every pack we produce, and we want you to be happy with your purchase. If you feel the sounds don't live up to what was described or previewed, please reach out and tell us specifically what the issue is — we take this feedback seriously. While we're unable to offer refunds based on change of mind (see our refund policy below), if there's a genuine quality concern we'll do everything we can to make it right, including offering credit toward another pack.</p>
        <a href="mailto:benntkmanagement@gmail.com?subject=Purchase%20Feedback" class="sp-item__link">Tell us about your experience →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q7 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">07</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">What is your refund policy?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>Because our products are delivered digitally and are immediately accessible upon purchase, all sales are final as a general policy. We're unable to issue refunds for change of mind, suitability concerns, or subjective preference. However, if you experience a genuine technical issue — such as corrupted files, a failed download, or missing content — contact us within 7 days of purchase with your order number and we'll resolve it promptly, either by re-delivering the files or issuing a replacement. We always aim to be fair.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q8 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">08</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">Can I use the sounds across multiple platforms at the same time?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>Yes — your Individual License covers unlimited platforms simultaneously. You can use the same sounds in a YouTube video, an Instagram Reel, a TikTok, a client deliverable, and a broadcast production all at the same time, with a single license. There's no per-platform fee and no limit on how many projects you use the sounds in concurrently. One purchase, unlimited use across everything you create.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q9 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">09</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">Do I need to credit Sonority Sound in my videos or content?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>No — attribution is never required. You're free to use the sounds in your content without crediting Sonority Sound in your description, captions, or anywhere else. That said, if you do choose to mention us we're always grateful — word of mouth is how independent sound libraries grow. But it's entirely optional and will never affect your license in any way.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Q10 -->
    <div class="sp-item" data-open="false">
      <button class="sp-item__q" aria-expanded="false">
        <span class="sp-item__num">10</span>
        <span class="sp-item__text">What file formats do I receive, and how do I download my purchase?</span>
        <span class="sp-item__icon">
          <svg class="sp-plus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="sp-minus" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="sp-item__a">
        <p>All Sonority Sound packs are delivered as high-quality WAV files — the industry standard for professional audio, compatible with every major editing software including Premiere Pro, Final Cut Pro, DaVinci Resolve, Logic Pro, and more. After completing your purchase you'll receive an email with a download link, and your files will also be accessible any time from your account. If you have any trouble downloading, contact us with your order number and we'll get it sorted immediately.</p>
        <a href="mailto:benntkmanagement@gmail.com?subject=Download%20Help" class="sp-item__link">Get help with your download →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Divider ── -->
  <div class="sp-divider">
    <span class="sp-divider__line"></span>
    <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1e1e1e" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 01-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2z"/></svg>
